data.description: A recent report indicates that the global economy is set to experience a growth rate of approximately 4.5% in the next year. This trend comes on the heels of a 3.5% growth rate this year. Furthermore, the report suggests that inflation is expected to remain steady at about 2.5%, with unemployment rates set to decrease to 5.2% globally. The rise in global trade is also predicted to continue, with an estimated increase of 6.5% in the upcoming year. These positive forecasts have been attributed to various factors, including increased consumer spending, advancements in technology, and government stimulus efforts. Overall, the economic outlook appears promising for the upcoming year.

data.title: Enterprise Products Partners' Q3 earnings dip with 61 cents/share (below est. 68 cents) and revenue drops 12.7% to $12.02 billion, showcasing lower prices impact. Gross operating margin at $2.4 billion in Q3 2025 vs. $2.5 billion in Q3 2024. Adjusted EBITDA at $2.41 billion vs. $2.44 billion in the same quarter last year.
data.description: Enterprise Products Partners L.P. reported lower third-quarter earnings due to decreased commodity prices and margins. Earnings were 61 cents/share, below the expected 68 cents, down from 65 cents/share last year. Quarterly revenue declined by 12.7% to $12.02 billion, slightly beating estimates of $11.93 billion. Gross operating margin was $2.4 billion, lower than last yearâ€™s $2.5 billion. Operating income fell to $1.69 billion from $1.78 billion, and adjusted EBITDA was $2.41 billion, compared to $2.44 billion last year. Distributable cash flow stood at $1.8 billion. Despite the weaker results, strong pipeline volumes and a major buyback expansion reflected long-term demand confidence.

data.title: Joyous launched by Chef Gabe Kennedy & Sodexo Seniors to enhance dining experience for seniors, addressing issue of 68% eating alone.
data.description: In Bethesda, Maryland, a new dining experience called Joyous is being introduced for senior residents in independent living environments. A survey revealed that around 80% of seniors desire more connection during meals, yet 68% currently eat alone. Backed by insights from Sodexo Seniors, a prominent provider of dining and management solutions for seniors, Joyous aims to address this issue. This innovative dining experience will feature culinary creations from a renowned chef and entrepreneur, fostering social engagement and community among residents.

data.title: Saudi Arabia's weight loss market expected to reach $2.7 billion by 2033 due to obesity rates and government efforts - ResearchAndMarkets.com.
data.description: A report on the "Saudi Arabia Weight Loss Market by Diet 2025-2033" has been included in ResearchAndMarkets.com's offerings. The market in Saudi Arabia is expected to experience substantial growth, increasing from USD 1.6 Billion in 2024 to USD 2.7 Billion by 2033, indicating a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 5.68% between 2025-2033. This growth is fueled by the escalating rates of obesity, attributed to lifestyle shifts due to urbanization and the rise in income from oil reserves in the region. Factors such as the adoption of Western dietary habits and a decrease in physical activities also contribute to this trend.

data.title: Carvana stock falls after mixed Q3 results: EPS $1.03 (missed estimates of $1.24), sales $5.64B, sold 155,941 units (44% YoY increase).
data.description: Carvana Co. (NYSE: CVNA) stocks are down after releasing their third-quarter financial results which were a mixed bag. The company faced a downturn in the market due to negative sentiment. For the third quarter, Carvana reported earnings per share of $1.03, falling short of the expected $1.24 as per Benzinga Pro. Despite this, the company surpassed sales expectations with total sales amounting to $5.64 billion instead of the anticipated $5.06 billion. In the same quarter, Carvana managed to sell 155,941 retail units, marking a significant 44% increase from the previous year, leading to a 55% year-over-year growth in total revenue. More details are accessible via Benzinga.com.

data.title: Google's Q3 results impress with $102.4 billion revenue, $35 billion net income, $2.87 EPS. Stock climbing. Analysts excited about AI momentum.
data.description: Alphabet, Inc. reported impressive Q3 results, surpassing expectations with total revenue reaching $102.4 billion â€“ the first quarter crossing $100 billion. Net income surged 33% to nearly $35 billion, and earnings per share rose to $2.87, a 35% jump. data.title: Satya Nadella redefines Microsoft's AI as a 'Token Factory,' boasting planet-scale efficiency. Company's AI data centers power GPT-5 training and Copilot queries, not reliant on single versions of Nvidia for all gigawatts.  Find full story on Benzinga.com.
data.description: In a recent earnings call, Satya Nadella presented a new metaphor for Microsoft Corp's (NASDAQ: MSFT) AI empire, referring to it as a "planet-scale token factory". This term describes the company's expansive global network of AI data centers, highlighting the efficiency of their operations. Nadella emphasized the continuous modernization of Microsoft's AI infrastructure, which supports various tasks such as GPT-5 training and Copilot queries. Unlike a singular vendor approach, Nadella explained that Microsoft's infrastructure is diversified for optimized performance. Investors can monitor MSFT stock performance closely. For more details, the full report is accessible on Benzinga.com.
